<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100557325595692></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100557325595692><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=578&mid=100557325595692>2hb & agro</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=578&mid=100557325595692#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=93579><span id=Scholar>Yosa</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>49 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Nov 12th 8:54 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.31]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>While hunting giants in RM I had the following converstation with a warrior 2 lvl lower then me.  <br><br>"Since I have better ac" he said, "You should let me tank."  <br>"Let you tank?"  I replied, "What weapons are you using?"<br>"A lam" and some other fast weapon, i forget the name.<br>"Seems to me that I shouldn't have to let you tank all I'm using is a Sarnack Battlehammer."<br><br>Now I didn't happen to menction the fbss I was wearing as well, but my point is don't assume that the faster weapon will always hold agro.  Before, this conversation I would of bet a Lam would of held agro.  I have seen more than one time that a good 2hb or 2hs has held agro.  As for getting mobs off cleric and casters, 8 out of 10 time in all the groups i was in over the weekend I was the one to regain agro after the mob attack a non melee.  <br><br>This is a great weapon, and there seems to be a lot of them for sell since the Chardock changes.  I payed 1000pp for mine and it is worth every cp.  <br><br>I was also part of a guild raid on RE.  We had two groups.  With me and the lam packing war as MA for the two diffrent groups.  When his group took on the MM he and to run for his life, do to the damage he took from the DS the MM has.  My group got there after the MM was back to full hit points.  We took him no problem, and I was never low on Hp. <br><br>All in all this is one of the better weapons in the game.  <br><br>Sure at higher lvl the lam will take the agro.  And speed will play a larger roll, but don't buy into the mith that speed always take agro.  More often than not at higher lvl speed equils more damage and that is why the faster weapons hold agro.  And for most weapons speed starts to take over between lvl 45 and 55.  <br><br>And sometime like when fighting a mob with a damage shield slow is better.  One other advantage i have noticed for two hand weapons, when fighting mobs that tend to run, the run with a lot less hp if you are using two hand weapon <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
